---
import SomeryLayout from "../../layouts/SomeryLayout.astro";
---

<SomeryLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Somery"
  description="Learn how Somery collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
>
  <section class="section legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: June 30, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-body reveal">
        <p>
          Somery ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This
          Privacy Policy explains what information we collect when you use the Somery iOS
          app, how we use it, and your rights regarding that information.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p><strong>Account information.</strong> When you create an account we collect
        your email address. You may also sign in with Google or Sign in with Apple, in
        which case those providers share a verified email address with us.</p>

        <p><strong>Dream journal entries.</strong> The personal text you write in the
        app, including any emotional content, mood, emotional state, sleep quality, and
        optional metadata you attach to entries.</p>

        <p><strong>HealthKit sleep data (optional).</strong> If you grant permission,
        Somery can read sleep duration and sleep stages from Apple HealthKit. This
        permission is entirely optional and can be revoked at any time in iOS Settings.
        We never write data back to HealthKit.</p>

        <p><strong>Anonymous usage analytics.</strong> We use Mixpanel and Firebase to
        collect anonymous, aggregated data about how features are used. These analytics
        events do not contain personally identifiable information or the content of your
        dream entries.</p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide and personalise the dream journaling experience.</li>
          <li>To generate AI interpretations of your dreams (see Section 3).</li>
          <li>To sync your data across devices via optional cloud backup.</li>
          <li>To improve the app through anonymous usage analytics.</li>
          <li>To communicate with you about your account when necessary.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. AI Processing</h2>
        <p>
          When you request an AI interpretation, the text of your dream entry is sent
          to OpenAI via Supabase Edge Functions. OpenAI processes the text to generate
          an interpretation and does not store your dream content beyond the immediate
          API call, per <a href="https://openai.com/policies/api-data-usage-policies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI's API data usage policy</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          AI interpretations are generated on Anthropic-hosted infrastructure. Dream
          visualisations (AI-generated images) are stored locally on your device and
          are not transmitted to any third-party image service.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
        <p><strong>On-device.</strong> Journal entries and dream visualisations are
        stored locally on your device using SwiftData. This data never leaves your
        device unless you enable cloud sync.</p>

        <p><strong>Cloud sync (optional).</strong> If you enable cloud backup, a copy
        of your profile and dream data is stored on Supabase (PostgreSQL). All data is
        protected with row-level security so only your account can access your records.
        You can disable cloud sync and delete your remote data at any time.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties. We share data
        only with the following service providers, and only to the extent necessary to
        operate the app:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — authentication and optional cloud database.</li>
          <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> — AI interpretation of dream content.</li>
          <li><strong>Google / Apple</strong> — if you choose to sign in with those providers.</li>
          <li><strong>Mixpanel &amp; Firebase</strong> — anonymous usage analytics.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each provider is bound by their own privacy policy and applicable data
        protection laws.</p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You can access, export, or delete your data at any time through
          <strong>Settings → Data Management</strong> inside the app. Deleting your
          account removes your data from our servers. Local SwiftData is deleted from
          your device when you uninstall the app or delete your account.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA) or United Kingdom, you
          have additional rights under the GDPR, including the right to data
          portability, rectification, and to lodge a complaint with a supervisory
          authority.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Somery is rated 12+ on the App Store. We do not knowingly collect personal
          information from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has
          provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will delete it
          promptly.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your data for as long as your account is active. If you delete your
          account, your data is removed from our servers within 30 days. Anonymous
          analytics data may be retained for up to 24 months.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use industry-standard measures to protect your data, including encryption
          in transit (TLS) and at rest, and row-level security in our database. No
          method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot
          guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of
          material changes by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
          Continued use of the app after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of
          the revised policy.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please
          contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@somery.app">privacy@somery.app</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SomeryLayout>
